**- What I did**
Added a new MachineConfigDaemon manager for InternalReleaseImage. 
Currently it takes care of updating the node MachineConfigNode with the status of the local IRI registry

**- How to verify it**
Run the iso-no-registry CI job

**- Description for the changelog**
todo

---

Example of MCN status update : 
```
 "internalReleaseImage": {
    "releases": [
      {
        "conditions": [
          {
            "lastTransitionTime": "2026-04-03T12:36:20Z",
            "message": "ReleaseImageAvailable",
            "reason": "ReleaseImageAvailable",
            "status": "False",
            "type": "Degraded"
          },
          {
            "lastTransitionTime": "2026-04-03T12:36:20Z",
            "message": "The specified release image is available",
            "reason": "ReleaseImageAvailable",
            "status": "True",
            "type": "Available"
          }
        ],
        "image": "127.0.0.1:22625/openshift/release-images@sha256:68bdf24405449be5c78a1f27a7b64fc9ee980e4bc3c9b169e8b3da08e50e0389",
        "name": "ocp-release-bundle-4.22.0-0.ci-2026-04-03-051414"
      }
    ]
  },
```

